definition: lit. to go upstream/to trace sth back to/to date from
to chase after/to seek/to do one's utmost to seek or procure sth/to recall
to go upstream/to trace the source

sentences.english: The history of those archaeologicalfinds goes back to the 2ndcentury.
sentences.chinese: 這些歷史文物的發現可追溯到2世紀。

sentences.english: Their friendship dates from college days.
sentences.chinese: 他們的友誼可追溯到大學時代。

sentences.english: Well, the reason I think essentially is again back to the civilization state.
sentences.chinese: 好吧，我認爲實質上，原因得再次追溯到這文明國家。

sentences.english: At present, the age of storm deposits reported in China may be traced back to late proterozoic.
sentences.chinese: 目前我國已報導的風暴沉積時代可追溯到晚元古代。

sentences.english: Some people's fear of marriage can be traced back to their parents' divorce. ;
sentences.chinese: 一些人對婚姻的驚駭可以追溯到他們怙恃的仳離。

sentences.english: Some sports or games go back thousands of years, like running or jumping.
sentences.chinese: 有些運動或運動會追溯到幾千年，如跑步或跳躍。

sentences.english: The development course of Pan-Turkism has been traced in the thesis.
sentences.chinese: 追溯了泛突厥主義發展的歷史。

sentences.english: The friendly relationship between the two countries traces back to the last century.
sentences.chinese: 兩國間的友好關係追溯到上個世紀。

sentences.english: Yep, going right back to the Bronze Age.
sentences.chinese: 沒錯，可以直接追溯至銅器時代。

sentences.english: Finally the article retraces the origin of the idea of the artistic innovation.
sentences.chinese: 最後本文追溯了這種藝術創新的觀念的由來。

sentences.english: Rifled firearms date at least to the 15th century.
sentences.chinese: 有膛線的武器最早可以追溯到15世紀。

sentences.english: Chopsticks originated in ancient China and dates back to as early as the Shang Dynasty.
sentences.chinese: 筷子的歷史起源於中國古代，最早可以追溯到商代。

sentences.english: Is the feature traceable to an original customer need?
sentences.chinese: 特徵能追溯到最初的用戶需要嗎？

sentences.english: In fact, the paintings have been dated back to around 13,000 BC.
sentences.chinese: 實際上，這些油畫大約要追溯到公元前一萬三千年。

definition: to investigate the origin of sth/to trace a river upstream back to its source
to pursue sth back to its origins/to trace back to the source/to get to the bottom of sth
to trace sth back to its origin
to keep/to preserve/extant/to remain (from the past)
see 追根溯源[zhui1 gen1 su4 yuan2]
to record/record (written account)/note-taker/record (in sports etc)/CL:個|个[ge4]
